From {{inh|en|enm|better}}, {{m|enm|bettre}}, {{m|enm|betre}}, from {{inh|en|ang|betera||better}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*batiʀō}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*batizô||better}}, from {{inh|en|ine-pro||*bʰed-rós}}, from {{m|ine-pro|*bʰed-||good}}.

Cognate with {{cog|sa|भद्र||tr=bhadrá|blessed, fortunate, happy, good}} (from {{m|ine-pro||*bʰn̥d-ró-s}}). For Germanic cognates: see {{m+|gem-pro|*batizô}}. Related to {{m|en|best}} and {{m|en|battle||getting better, improving, fruitful, fertile}}. Compare also {{cog|is|batna||to improve}}, {{m|is|bót||improvement}}, {{cog|de|besser}}. More at {{m|en|batten}}, {{m|en|boot}}.

{{cog|fa|بهتر}} is a false cognate.

